		"description": "<p>Unlike flame bracers, flamethrowers are military-grade weapons that project wide swaths of flame. As an action, you can choose between a 30-foot line that is 5 feet wide or a 15-foot cone. Each creature in that area takes 2d6 fire damage, or half as much damage on a successful Dexterity saving throw. The DC of this save is 8 + your proficiency modifier + your Dexterity modifier. Unattended flammable objects in the area are ignited.</p>",
